  "kuerzel": "M_SEProj",
  "bezeichnung": "SE Project",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>All participants are able to execute a medium-sized software development project in a team, using a systematic engineering approach and modern state-of-the-art methods and tools.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>All participants need to be able to demonstrate the effective application of selected practices from the following disciplines:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business modelling</li>\n<li>Requirements</li>\n<li>Analysis and design</li>\n<li>Implementation</li>\n<li>Verification</li>\n<li>Deployment</li>\n<li>Configuration and change management</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The taxonomy and format of the Unified Process (UP) and the Unified Modelling Language (UML) will be used whenever appropriate.</p>",
  "vorausgKenntnisse": "<ul>\n<li>Attending the module SE Practices 2 in parallel to this module is required.</li>\n<li>Being able to successfully form a team is a prerequisite for this module.</li>\n</ul>",
  "semesterBewertung": "Note von 1 - 6",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "aktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 43713,
      "kuerzel": "SEProj",
      "bezeichnung": "SE Project",
      "lernziele": "<p>Refer to the learning goals for the module.</p>",
      "planinhalt": "<p>All participants will be required to execute a medium-sized software development project from inception through to deployment.</p>\n<p>Each participant is required to form a team of 4 to 5 participants. Being able to successfully form a team is a prerequisite for this course.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each team is assigned an advisor who keeps track of the team's progress over a number of review meetings.</p>\n<p><br />At the end of the project, each team is required to present their project to the rest of the participants and submit all project artefacts.</p>",
